%% StudyFlow — Document Upload & Analysis Flow
%% Shows what happens when a student uploads a file and it's auto-classified

sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor Student as 👩‍🎓 Student
  participant Web as 🌐 Web App
  participant API as ⚙️ Next.js API
  participant S3 as 🗄️ Object Storage
  participant PG as 🐘 Postgres
  participant Queue as 📬 Redis Queue
  participant Detect as 📄 Detector Worker
  participant AI as 🤖 Gemini

  Student->>Web: Upload PDF / drag & drop
  Web->>API: POST /api/files (signed URL request)
  API->>S3: Request signed upload URL
  S3-->>API: Signed URL
  API-->>Web: Signed URL + file_id
  Web->>S3: PUT file bytes
  Web->>API: POST /api/files/:id/ingest
  API->>PG: Insert file (status=uploaded)
  API->>Queue: Enqueue detect_type job
  API-->>Web: 202 Accepted (pending)

  Queue->>Detect: Pull detect_type job
  Detect->>S3: Fetch file
  Detect->>AI: Classify (lecture/practice/homework) + extract structure
  AI-->>Detect: { type: "homework", questions: [...] }
  Detect->>PG: Update file.type + questions
  Detect->>Queue: Enqueue post-processing per type
  Note over Queue: homework → analyze_questions<br/>lecture → summarize<br/>practice → extract_exercises

  Detect->>Web: WebSocket: file.analyzed event
  Web->>Student: Show "Homework detected · 8 questions" UI
  Student->>Web: Click "Open Homework Workspace"
  Web->>API: GET /api/files/:id/questions
  API->>PG: Fetch questions
  API-->>Web: Questions payload
  Web->>Student: Render Homework Workspace with navigation
